\begin_layout Standard
Primero veamos qué debe ocurrir para que 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 sea una 
\series bold
variación
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Observamos que es claramente diferenciable, ya que 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 es una curva regular y 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 es diferenciable.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Por tanto, solo resta asegurar que 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi\left(s,0\right)=\alpha\left(s\right),\ \forall s\in I$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\phi\left(s,0\right)=\alpha\left(s\right)+\left(0,0,f\left(s,0\right)\right)=\alpha\left(s\right)\iff f\left(s,0\right)=0,\ \forall s\in I
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Para que sea 
\series bold
propia
\series default
:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\alpha\left(a\right)=\phi\left(a,t\right)=\alpha\left(a\right)+\left(0,0,f\left(a,t\right)\right)\iff f\left(a,t\right)=0,\ \forall t\in\left(-\varepsilon,\varepsilon\right)
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\alpha\left(b\right)=\phi\left(b,t\right)=\alpha\left(b\right)+\left(0,0,f\left(b,t\right)\right)\iff f\left(b,t\right)=0,\ \forall t\in\left(-\varepsilon,\varepsilon\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Y, por último, para que sea 
\series bold
normal
\series default
, calculamos 
\begin_inset Formula $Z\left(s\right)$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Z\left(s\right)=\frac{\partial\phi}{\partial t}\left(s,0\right)=\frac{\partial}{\partial t}|_{t=0}\phi\left(s,t\right)=\left(0,0,\frac{\partial f}{\partial t}\left(s,t\right)\right)|_{t=0}=\left(0,0,\frac{\partial}{\partial t}f\left(s,0\right)\right)\in\left[T_{\alpha\left(s\right)}S\right]^{\perp}
\]

\end_inset

 por lo que es normal siempre, independientemente de 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Así, tenemos que 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 es una variación propia y normal si, y solo si, 
\begin_inset Formula $f\left(s,0\right)=f\left(a,t\right)=f\left(b,t\right)=0,\ \forall s\in I,t\in\left(-\varepsilon,\varepsilon\right)$
\end_inset

, tal y como queríamos demostrar.
\end_layout

